### Reproduction Steps

1. Run the attached sample in Release mode.
2. Click the "Call LINQ Queries" button.
3. Take a memory snapshot and observe that ObjectEqualityComparer<GridColumn> is retained.
4. Click the "Dispose List" button.
5. Take another snapshot and observe that ObjectEqualityComparer<GridColumn> is still retained even after disposing.

### Expected behavior

The ObjectEqualityComparer<CustomColumn> object should not be retained in the memory profiler as a leak.

### Actual behavior

The ObjectEqualityComparer<CustomColumn> object is retained in the memory profiler as a leak.

